cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with acoustic scene classification and sound event detection.
- cs.SI (Speech and Natural Language Processing) is also likely as the paper involves processing audio signals and extracting features for classification.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses classifier optimization and heuristics specific to each task.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper involves developing algorithms for classification tasks.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper deals with real-life recordings and processing of audio signals.
